article.headline: Georgetown 76, Winston-Salem 32
article.story: WASHINGTON (AP) -- Jessie Sapp and DaJuan Summers each scored 14 points and Roy Hibbert added 10 points as Georgetown ran away in the second half for a 76-32 victory over Winston-Salem State on Saturday night. Slow out of the gate, the Hoyas (7-3) went on a 30-1 run in the second half, holding the Rams without a field goal for nearly 11 minutes. Tyler Crawford chipped in with 12 points for the Hoyas. The Rams (1-13) were led by Darius Floyd with 11 points. Georgetown's 27-18 halftime lead was cut to six with 17:12 remaining in the game. Following a time-out, Crawford started the Hoyas' run with a 3-pointer, one of three he would hit during the run. Sapp and Summers each scored 10 points in the second half as the Hoyas shot 70 percent in the second half. The Hoyas scored 13 straight points midway through the first half to open up a 27-10 lead, capped off by a Summers alley-oop dunk. The Rams came back with the final eight points of the half and continued the surge in the opening moments of the second half before the Hoyas took control. The Hoyas won their third straight game after having lost two straight and falling out of the top 25. They return to the Verizon Center next Wednesday when they take on Towson. The Rams, who are in their second year at the Division 1 level, dropped their 10th straight contest.
